Subject: [PATCH] mtmd: fix gemma4a audio crash (missing GEMMA4A in clip_n_mmproj_embd)

clip_n_mmproj_embd() lacks a PROJECTOR_TYPE_GEMMA4A case, so a Gemma-4
mmproj with an audio projector (clip.audio.projector_type = "gemma4a")
falls through to `default: GGML_ABORT("Unknown projector type")` and
aborts the process (SIGABRT) during audio encoder warmup.

GEMMA4A is handled in every other projector switch in clip.cpp
(load_tensors, the graph builder dispatch, n_patches, etc.); it is only
missing from clip_n_mmproj_embd(). Group it with its sibling audio
variant GEMMA4UA, which already returns hparams.projection_dim. This is
the correct value: for the Gemma-4 E4B mmproj, clip.audio.projection_dim
== gemma4.embedding_length (2560), which is what clip_n_mmproj_embd must
return so the audio embeddings can be injected into the text model.

Refs: #21325
---
 tools/mtmd/clip.cpp | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/tools/mtmd/clip.cpp b/tools/mtmd/clip.cpp
--- a/tools/mtmd/clip.cpp
+++ b/tools/mtmd/clip.cpp
@@ -4381,6 +4381,7 @@ int clip_n_mmproj_embd(const struct clip_ctx * ctx) {
             return ctx->model.mm_fc_w->ne[1];
         case PROJECTOR_TYPE_LFM2A:
             return ctx->model.position_embeddings->ne[0];
+        case PROJECTOR_TYPE_GEMMA4A:
         case PROJECTOR_TYPE_GEMMA4UA:
             return ctx->model.hparams.projection_dim;
         case PROJECTOR_TYPE_GRANITE_SPEECH:
